<subSubSection id="1EBF4134B8483934C038D74A5E858508" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="30EF2C331AB5950FA590FCB40CDF7D58" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="CBC8BB045963D54F10949518864D41F6" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">
The epithet &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="23453CB8A26ABA059562B7E5309B82E8" authorityName="M. N. Tamayo, R. Bustam. &amp; P. W. Fritsch" authorityYear="2021" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Vaccinium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Vaccinium exiguum" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="exiguum">
<emphasis id="ABA9EDBA763FF44D217430AFAB39D8BD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">Vaccinium exiguum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
&quot; refers to the overall small stature and leaf morphology of the new species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="02456B62C5AA293FA219887AC93C2559" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="371BF19EEA7E70A680ED02104EF23155" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">Distribution and habitat.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="12FEE40EA2AD4661C40B5D50A024ECA1" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">
<taxonomicName id="5A8891147F9A28907BA1616DCD386D31" authorityName="M. N. Tamayo, R. Bustam. &amp; P. W. Fritsch" authorityYear="2021" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Vaccinium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Vaccinium exiguum" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="exiguum">
<emphasis id="671F1A29DC66747CEF7B3647FE9E548F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">Vaccinium exiguum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is currently known from a single individual from a single location at the exposed ultramafic forest summit of Mt. Victoria, Palawan Island, Philippines at ca. 1700 m elevation.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="5546131CB67F4B6CDA2BD56C53305718" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" type="conservation status">
<paragraph id="B1EA2C1318944EA5C763A304C793AA95" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">Conservation status.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="611C2233175355535622420DE7F182C5" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">
Only a single flowering plant was documented from a single location at the summit of Mt. Victoria, Palawan. Other summits within the mountain range are similar to the type locality in elevation, but these have yet to be explored. As such, we propose the conservation threat status Data Deficient (DD) (
<bibRefCitation id="6BBB697EE786E367F8CA7C5F90B6CE77" author="IUCN Standards and Petitions Committee" journalOrPublisher="Linnean Society of London" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" publicationUrl="http://www.iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuidelines.pdf" refId="B12" refString="IUCN Standards and Petitions Committee, 2019. Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 14. Prepared by the Standards and Petitions Committee. Available from: http://www.iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuidelines.pdf" title="Guidelines for Using the IUCN Red List Categories and Criteria. Version 14. Prepared by the Standards and Petitions Committee. Available from:" url="http://www.iucnredlist.org/documents/RedListGuidelines.pdf" year="2019">IUCN Standards and Petitions Committee 2019</bibRefCitation>
) due to the scarcity of data with which to confidently assess the species against the IUCN guidelines.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8D942D989BF867BBB570CAD8A17E58BC" pageId="0" pageNumber="145">
Many species are endemic to Mt. Victoria (
<bibRefCitation id="EC8531097CC6AC83E3F6EC95335F5699" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1095-8339.2008.00942.x" author="Robinson, AS" journalOrPublisher="Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" pagination="195 - 202" refId="B19" refString="Robinson, AS, Fleischmann, AS, McPherson, SR, Heinrich, VB, Gironella, EP, Pena, CQ, 2009. A spectacular new species of Nepenthes L. (Nepenthaceae) pitcher plant from central Palawan, Philippines. Botanical Journal of the Linnean Society 159 (2): 195 - 202, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1095-8339.2008.00942.x" title="A spectacular new species of Nepenthes L. (Nepenthaceae) pitcher plant from central Palawan, Philippines." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1095-8339.2008.00942.x" volume="159" year="2009">Robinson et al. 2009</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="0B8FBF89918A2C71C6798DD5389EC16E" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.252.2.2" author="Robinson, AS" journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="145" pagination="99 - 113" refId="B20" refString="Robinson, AS, Gironella, EP, Cervancia, JM, 2016. New orchid species of Stigmatodactylus (Orchidoideae; Diurideae) and a new record of Cryptostylis carinata from central Palawan, Philippines. Phytotaxa 252 (2): 99 - 113, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.252.2.2" title="New orchid species of Stigmatodactylus (Orchidoideae; Diurideae) and a new record of Cryptostylis carinata from central Palawan, Philippines." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/phytotaxa.252.2.2" volume="252" year="2016">2016</bibRefCitation>
). Though harboring high biodiversity, Mt. Victoria is unfortunately not legislated as a protected area (PA). Mining activities within the area are considered a significant threat that poses the risk of habitat and forest degradation. Thus, the lack of legal protection is the greatest threat to this species and to the biodiversity of the area.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
